description.narrative:
With support from the Swedish International Development Cooperation Agency (Sida), UN Women conducted a study on Congolese women's participation in the electoral process in the DRC. The following are examples of the outcomes:
• UN Women conducted research in 5 provinces to identify the root causes of women’s low representation and influence in politics and compiled the results in a study. This led to the development of a roadmap and a multiyear programme of activities to increase women's political participation and capacity, including training of local women involved in politics;
• UN Women trained 48 Deputies from the Kinshasa Provincial Assembly on Gender and gender mainstreaming in parliamentary functions;
• UN Women supported the establishment of DYNAFEC, a network gathering politically active women, in 8 provinces. UN Women supported the establishment of the African Women Leadership Network regional chapter in Kananga;
• UN Women organized an online training for more than 60 provincial parliamentarians, which led to the creation of a network for exchange between the parliamentarians.
